<section props="page-margin-footer:0.5in; page-margin-header:0.5in">
<p style="Heading 1">Insert Table Dialog</p>
<p style="Normal">Insert a new table into your document.</p>
<p style="Heading 2">Table Size</p>
<p style="Normal">The numbers selected here fix the dimensions of the table you insert. It is possible to insert or delete rows and columns later; see the <a xlink:href="menutable.html">Table menu</a>.</p>
<p style="Heading 3">Number of Columns:</p>
<p style="Normal">The number of columns you wish this table to have.</p>
<p style="Heading 3">Number of Rows:</p>
<p style="Normal">The number of rows you wish this table to have.</p>
<p style="Heading 2">AutoFit Behavior</p>
<p style="Heading 3"><c></c>Automatic column size</p>
<p style="Normal">This option splits the available width equally amongst all of the columns.</p>
<p style="Heading 3">Fixed column width</p>
<p style="Normal">This option allows you to set a specific width for columns. Change the column size either by typing in the box or clicking on the up and down arrows to its right.</p>
<p style="Heading 2">Help</p>
<p style="Normal">This button opens the documentation for this dialog.</p>
<p style="Heading 2"><c></c>Cancel</p>
<p style="Normal">This button closes the dialog without inserting a new table.</p>
<p style="Heading 2">Insert</p>
<p style="Normal">This button inserts a new table into the document and closes the dialog.</p>
</section>
